SIMPLE: unappealable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unappealable
<hw>Un`ap*peal"a*ble</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not
appealable; that can not be carried to a higher tribunal by appeal;
<as>as, an <ex>unappealable</ex> suit or action</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not to be appealed from; -- said of a judge or a
judgment that can not be overruled.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The infallible, <qex>unappealable</qex> Judge [God].</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We submitted to a galling yet <qex>unappealable</qex>
necessity.</q> <rj><qau>Shelley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Un`ap*peal"a*bly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unappliable</ent>⟦br⟧
